						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Broken stone built into the piel of the Lingāyata maṭha.</hi></p>						

						<p>[Jaitugi]—A.D. 1194.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged and effaced record is dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1115, Pramādi, Māgha, Monday, Śivarātri,</hi> regularly corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1194, February 21, Monday.</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription begins with a <hi rend="italic">vachana</hi> of Kapilasiddha Mallikārjuna and records a gift of a village (name lost) for the worship of the god Kapilasiddha-Mallikārjuna of <hi rend="bold">Sonnalige</hi> by <hi rend="bold">Māyidēva-Daṇṇāyaka</hi> (<hi rend="italic">i.e.</hi> Daṇḍanāyaka).</p>						

						</summary>
